inn1.comm: away first ball, clipping the fullish ball off pad through midwicket
pitched up again, on middle and off, patted back down the pitch
length ball around off stump, he likes the leg side, shuffles across and turns it towards leg, bowler fields
angles it across the left-hander now, good length, allows it to go past
pitched up and angled across, he goes for the drive through extra cover, beaten
similar delivery, pitched up further, this time he shoulders arms
swings in first up into the pads, good full length, appeal for lbw as Hafeez misses the flick, going down leg comfortably
this time Hafeez gets hold of the full length and the inswing into the pads, whips past square leg, the ball slows down near the rope, and fine leg gets around to it
good length now, moving in once again, this time he nudges it to fine leg
short to Jamshed now, outside off stump, easily avoided
good length, angled in from over the stumps, ending on off, pushed towards mid on
way too wide outside off, short of a length, moves further away, almost a Test-match wide
much fuller, closer to off, swinging away late, squeezed out to cover
right on off stump, length ball, he bends forward and blocks
short and wide, Hafeez gets on his toes and slaps it to point, mistimed it
played out to square leg with the angle into him
leans across to a length ball on middle stump, worked out towards mid on
another one short and wide, this time he times the slap quite well, in front of cover, Maxwell gets in the dive to his right and saves some runs
pitched up widish, and that has been crashed through covers, the fielder put in a dive but it whizzed past him, Jamshed getting front foot out and going powerfully at the drive
punch off the back foot, and that is a fine sprint at mid off, ending in a tumble which stops the ball which was buzzing along at some pace
length ball played out to point
angles it in fullish, 137.6 kph, forced out to mid on
short, into the body, and Jamshed is ready with the pull, swivels and lifts it over square leg from just above waist height
another four, Jamshed gets a pitched up delivery into the pads, and whips it crisply in the air in front of square leg
another very wide one, moved away further from back of a length outside off
moves away again, back of a length again, but tighter line outside off, left alone

that is ridiculous, that is a top edge that has almost gone for six over fine third man, Hafeez through with the pull a shade too early outside leg, gets the top edge close to the top end, steepler falls just before the boundary
another loose shot, Hafeez leans across to an inswinging length ball, hits it dangerously in the air towards mid on, falls short
defended off the front foot
back of a length, and another one in the air for a while, falling short of midwicket
all subcontinent batsmen love that line, length into the pads, and Hafeez happily tucks it past square leg
pitched up, he opens up in the crease and nudges to midwicket
swings away fullish, around off, reaches out to push to point
gets across and pushes back down the pitch
swings away full and late, widish outside off, he reaches out and dabs it to point
off the pads and the single is prevented by short fine to his right
slower one, full at 116 kph, pushed away softly to extra cover

short ball banged in, Jamshed hurried into the stroke, and another of those top-edged pulls that become steeplers over third man results, Pattinson rushes in, and stretches to his right to slap the ball back in on the bounce one-handed, and then tumbles over the rope, outstanding
worked to square leg off the pad
full and moving in, dug back to the bowler
bounce at 140 kph from back of a length, he goes for the cut and is beaten
moves across, hops and punches awkwardly to covers
right on middle, good length, he goes back and across, behind the line, blocks
the yorker, on the stumps, Hafeez leans across and digs it out
pitched up, some late away swing from the left-hander, mistimed drive to short extra cover
pushed firmly to mid off
good length, angled in with a lot of shoulder down the leg side
fine bouncer around off, he drops the wrists, bends the knee and weaves out of the way

lovely, gets forward to a pitched up ball, and caresses it past extra cover with a graceful followthrough, "magnificent, majestic", Ramiz Raja gets the adjectives out on air, as it slows down near the rope
left alone outside off as it moves away from short of a length
length ball on a tight line on off, he bends forward and keeps it out
gets across and outside  off and awkwardly defends a back of a length ball
gets forward and pushes towards mid off
another one on the pads, and it is worked wristily behind square leg, deep square gets around
can't get it away, moves across and opens up to a length ball angled in, but has to push it towards mid on
wow, now he tries a scoop from outside off, it rolls away towards point
tries to pull, but cannot get hold of the short ball well as it comes slowly off the pitch, mistimes the shot into the ground
that is a sharp short ball, at nearly 147 kph, surprises him with the lift and bite, he hops and fends it in the air in front of point
full, speared into the pads, flicked with nice timing to deep square
superb one-handed stop to his left by Clarke at cover
moves across and outside off, pushes softly to short cover
tossed up from round the stumps, he winds up and crashes it, Warner dives to his left at extra cover and stops the stinger
nudged with the spin behind square leg
some spin just outside off, good length, pushed towards covers
down the track and eases it past midwicket to wide long on
drives a full delivery to sweeper cover, easily done
well done, dabs it very late just past the keeper, short third man is around
driven off the front foot to cover
bounce, lots of it, from back of a length, too close to cut or steer, Hafeez tries to, and is beaten
opens the face and runs a length ball straight to backward point, quite a struggle for Hafeez right now
beaten for pace on the pull, 142 kph, off the thigh pad into the off side
lenght ball, he pushes softly into the gap between cover and point, Jamshed had to hurry up in the end as the throw came in
short, but miles down the leg side, he thinks to swing it around the corner for a moment, lets it go
full on the pads and worked to fine leg
offspinner coming in gently, pushed back to the bowler
reaches forward and across, and paddles it from outside off to fine leg
driven hard but straight to extra cover
flighted ball driven to cover
defended to the off side
moves forward and across, couple of steps out, pushes to off
too wide outside off, he reaches out and dabs it past point for one to sweeper cover
pitched up, gets forward and pushes to mid off
moves across and tightly defends a length ball to leg
not exactly short, but Jamshed has some width outside off to swat it down to wide long on
walks down the pitch and outside off and looks to swing it through midwicket, the back of a length ball hits him on thigh pad, quite loud and too optimistic an appeal for lbw
length ball pushed out towards extra cover
fetches it from way outside off and sweeps it in front of square leg, man runs across hard from deep midwicket and saves the boundary
moves down the track and eases it to long off
flat outside off, slapped away to sweeper cover
goes for the reverse sweep to a ball way outside off, it turns in slightly, beats bat, and beats keeper
comes down the pitch, takes it low on the full and eases it through midwicket
drives a pitched up outside off to extra cover
moves across, and a couple of paces out, works it from middle through midwicket
pushed to covers
back of a length, punched in front of point
stays in the crease, and works it from around off to a diving midwicket
very tough chance, dropped by the bowler, Hafeez clobbered a pitched up ball high to the bowler's left, he got a hand to it, but there was really too much zip on the stroke, mid off fields
fired in on middle, defended hurriedly
punched past a diving bowler to long on
comes down the pitch, gets too close to the pitch, and eases it down to long off
worked from off stump straight to square leg
that has been fired in round-armish from round the stumps, way down the leg side, little chance for the keeper, rolls off his gloves
pushed back to the bowler
fullish, around off, pushed out to the man at cover
comes in from a good length outside off, cramped for room a bit, runs it to point
charges out, has a swing, and an inside edge runs past the stumps to fine leg
moves in again onto the stumps, thick inside edge on to pad and to square leg
length ball angled across, pushed firmly to sweeper cover
squeezes a slower one, 110 kph, full and wide outside off, to third man
a few paces down the pitch and pushes softly to mid off
well wide with the angle from wide of the crease down leg
digs out a full one outside off to point
pushes a pitched up ball down to mid on for a single
moves across and defends one one a tight line just around off
pitched up full, on the stumps, he pushes hard down the pitch, bowler fields
into the pads, good length, nudged behind square
pitched up, he tries to drive but gets too close to the line, is cramped outside off, and mistimes the stroke
slower one, bowled full outside off, and he ends up pushing in the air, well short of cover though,
pitched full again outside off, and driven with an open face down to square third man,  hint of straightening in the air late on the delivery
bowled full, and Hafeez attacks it, does not quite get hold of the swing, and the ball swirls high over point, and third man eventually gets around to it, quite a stubborn outfield this
poor line, fired in full and wide down the pads, whipped away happily in the air to the fine leg rope
very full outside off, and squeezed out to point
nicely bowled, almost in the blockhole around off, dabbed softly down to third man

that is an outstanding stroke from a batsman who has struggled for timing throughout his innings, short of a length, almost as if he was waiting for it, Hafeez stands in the crease and wallops it high over midwicket, there is a man in the deep, he can fetch it back
worked to midwicket
this one did not get up all that much, but Hafeez controlled the pull very well, along the ground through square leg, off the toe end of the bat
opens the face and runs it with the angle across him to third man
ends up hitting it in the air towards vacant mid on as he shuffles across to a length ball
shot! this man has very fast reaction time, not that short, on the pads, he explodes into a violent pull and sends it behind square leg
widish length ball, he reaches out and dabs it towards point
bit close but authoritative, down the track, makes some room for the swing, and lofts the length ball over extra cover, who leaps but in vain
sent wide down the leg side now
again on the pads, worked to short fine leg for the 100-run stand
walks across and works a full ball from off through square leg
growing in audacity all the time, another charge out, this time he drills it down to wide long off
important fifty for the Pakistan T20 captain brought up with a push down the ground on the leg side, acknowledges the cheers, calmly raises the bat
crunch! length ball, Hafeez takes a step forward and murders it high and straight down the ground
into the pads, misses the work to square, slight appeal from the bowler, that was headed clearly down leg
beaten for pace, 140 kph, on the back of a length ball as he tries to swivel and swing it behind square leg
down the leg side now
worked with the angle into him through midwicket
makes room outside leg and cracks the length ball straight to extra cover
makes room again, this time just dabs a length ball to square third man
pushes a full ball from round the stumps to long off
batsman beaten after an age, playing for spin into him outside off, it hurries past the outside edge
this time he does not commit forward, stays in the crease and dabs to short third
eep, helpful full toss, and Hafeez lunges forward and swipes it hard through square leg
one more, even a big dive in the deep cannot stop the boundary, Hafeez gets forward and sweeps forcefully again, in the air, and beats deep midwicket running across
full, played out to extra cover
moves across and punches a length ball down to long on
getting right forward now, very confidently, eases it wide of mid off, and they take a sharp run
played out from the crease towards point, Hafeez races up for the single, is sent back, Jamshed looks a bit knackered
bouncer arrives, 140 kph, Jamshed ducks under it
tidy line around off, pushed firmly off the front foot to sweeper cover
allows a pitched up ball to angle in and runs it to point
worked to midwicket
not that short, he arches back and pulls hard, one bounce to deep midwicket
pushed back to the bowler from middle
pushed down the ground to long off
makes some room and guides it behind point, sweeper gets around
pats a nippy length ball down the pitch

appeal for caught behind down the leg side as Jamshed misses a pull off a short ball angled in, Clarke going upstairs, neat take from the keeper to his right, it has flicked the shirt just above the waist, that caused the sound, and Australia lose the review
another short ball, and this time he's got him, Mitch smiles widely, sharp sharp bouncer head high, Jamshed tried to hook, keeper takes it safely
angled across, wide outside off, too far
smash! the crowd loves it, Afridi takes a step out and bashes a length ball high over extra cover, no outfield, slow enough, stops it when boom boom hits 'em
and then has a flail at a wide ball going across, cannot connect
pitched up full outside off, and powered down to long off
bowled full and across outside off, driven past a diving extra cover to wide long off
swivels furiously but hits the pull to midwicket, is cross he found the fielder
slower one, 110 kph, pops up in the air towards long off as he pushes at it
fine shot, drives a full delivery from round the stumps down to long on
tries to pull a slow short ball from outside off, is in the air, a bit like Nadal playing a topspin forehand, mistimed to midwicket
length ball down to third man for one
widish full one pushed to sweeper cover
short ball hammered straight to deep midwicket, sigh, that is it for the crowd, pulling off the front foot, and picking out deep midwicket perfectly
driven to extra cover off the front foot
left alone outside off
bounces and kicks outside off, he is surprised by the lift and runs it to third man
flat outside off, runs it behind point
spins in and is worked in front of square leg
pushed down to long on
a reverse paddle off a low full toss on off, short third man fields
gets forward and works with the spin to square leg
goes wide of the crease, angles it in full, worked to midwicket
short of a length, width outside off, cut to sweeper cover
144.2 kph short ball dug into the body, pulled through square leg, the ball hits close to the gloves, but he handled it alright in the end
pitched full from over the stumps now, pushed to extra cover
straightens down the leg side, a sounds as it passes the batsman on its way to the keeper, no appeal, probably thigh pad
bends the knee and drives off the front foot to extra cover
not that short, and he ends up mistiming the pull into the ground through midwicket
opens up and punches a flat one to long on
quite wide outside off, not given one, he is beaten on the cut
pushed down to long on
gets hold of it and cuts behind point for a couple as the sweeper gets around
comes forward and eases a full one down the pitch, bowler dives to his right to field
slippery flat one, cuts from very close to off stump to backward point

loud appeal and Clarke strikes second ball, big strike too, Hafeez lunging forward to paddle a full delivery, missed, and was struck in front of middle and off, given by the umpire, Hafeez reviews, not much doubt about that one, Pakistan lose Hafeez and the review too
attacks his first ball hard outside off, cuts it straight to point though
right forward, bat beside pad to defend around off
reaches out and pushes off the front foot to extra cover
flighted, he lunges forward and defends down the pitch
rocks back and bashes it back to the bowler
neat, dabs late and from close to the stumps fine past the keeper
goes back and works through square leg
reverse sweeps from well outside off, to short third man
reverse sweep once again, and this time wide enough of short third man
missed stumping chance, Clarke beats him with lots of flight outside off, he drives expecting the turn, it goes straight, keeper fails to collect, back foot was out for some time
paddled fine from around off
full, driven towards mid off
lunges right forward, thick inside edge to leg, Shafiq sends him back as he comes out for a run
comes across and whips it from off, straight to midwicket
length into the pads and worked past short fine for a couple
on the pads again, again he tucks it wide of short fine, who runs across and slides to stop it
moves in to middle off a length, worked to midwicket
another one angled in sharply, has to be some plan, a sound as it passes the batsman on its way to the keeper, probably thigh pad
down to long on for a single
shapes in from a good length outside off, punched to long on
full, driven off the front foot through extra cover
on the pads, good length, nudged past midwicket
wide delivery, slower one, dabbed straight to point
goes for the pull to a short of a length ball on leg, hits it into the ground towards square leg
comes down the pitch and outside off, works a length ball to midwicket
driven forcefully off the front foot wide of mid off
slower one curls in, beats him as he tries to cut
charges out, Christian angles it in, Misbah can only force it to extra cover, direct hit would have tested Shafiq
whipped away off the pads, beats short fine leg, and has enough pace on it to win the chase
hit hard to mid off, throw misses at the non-striker's, and they take the overthrow as well
thew everything at the slower one close to off, trying to heave over midwicket, and missed
near-yorker around off, squeezed out in front of cover for a sharp run
angled in wide down leg from round the stumps
length ball whipped from middle to deep midwicket
fuller, worked to midwicket
flicked straight to short fine leg, angled in on a length into the pads from round the stumps, he plays the stroke with a flourish and finds the fielder, walks back disappointed
hops and prods at a back of a length ball angled in, beaten
that is a wicket thrown away, second ball to the crease, Umar Akmal wants to power a short ball over deep midwicket, hits it straight to the man in the deep
worked square on the leg side
defends a sharp length ball to point
super flick, in the air, but timed so well behind square leg that deep square and fine leg had no chance
behind the line of a good length ball on off and middle to block
reaches out and runs a widish one to third man
could have been a wide had he not reached out and dug out the very full one
gets on his toes and works a back of a length ball to fine leg
reaches out and pushes a wide and full one to extra cover
plays out a back of a length ball down the pitch
works a length ball angled in, to midwicket
pushed off the front foot to extra cover
tries to drive down the ground, gets it off the inner part of the bat down the pitch
slow length ball, nudged to midwicket
short and bouncing outside off, he hops in the air and runs it to third man softly
some width, he runs it down to third man
full, he squeezes a drive down the pitch, bowler gets a hand to it, mid off tidies up
swinging in a bit, ending on off, cannot do anything but nudge it down the pitch
punched off the back foot to sweeper cover
drives a wide delivery nicely past point, sweeper runs across to field
superb timing on the cut, wide and he flashes at it with fast hands, and third man has little chance
bat in front of pad to work it off middle to midwicket
full, he pushes straight to extra cover
runs a widish back of a length ball to third man
worked square on leg from around off
cut to deep point
worked from middle down to deep midwicket
offcutter, whipped from well outside off now through midwicket
drives a wide and full one to sweeper cover
shuffles across and digs out a yorker to midwicket
full ball, and another single through midwicket
squeezes a full one to point
Bailey at point runs to his left and dives to field, but the single is on
driven off the front foot wide of extra cover
neatly done, the short ball came slowly off the pitch, he waited and dabbed it to third man
walks down the pitch, turns a full ball into a yorker and jams it to off
full, driven off the front foot to extra cover
hits a low full toss hard to deep midwicket
gets forward and runs a widish one to short third
chops a cut hard to point
low full toss whipped to deep midwicket
can't find any timing on the slog down the ground, and bowler fields with a lunge to his right
swings a full toss from the stumps to long on
holes out to long off, pitched up full, Misbah winds up for the big swing but mistimes it for the fielder to come in and take it
arches back and steers a back of a length ball to third man
short, he walks across outside the line and drags it just out of the keeper's reach down leg
lovely delivery, angled in from round the stumps, and just about holds its line to beat the outside edge as Kamran leans out
another beauty, Starc is wound up, he is visibly tired, but he produces another ripper, angled in again, straightens just enough to beat the forward push and this time, it strikes off
defends a length ball around off
worked from outside off down to long on
flails at a wide one from the crease and misses
beats the outside edge now, has him coming forward to a length ball which just holds its line a bit
digs out a very full one wide of point
full, driven hard through the bowler's hands down to long off
opens the face and squeezes a length ball to third man
angled in wide down leg from over the stumps
comes out and drives through extra cover
flashes at a not-so-wide one outside off and gets it fine and wide of third man
run out chance, Rehman had given up, Maxwell ran in from extra cover, dived forward and lobbed the ball towards the non-striker's stumps, missed
drives hard to extra cover and rushes down for the single throw misses again
very effective in the end, Rehman walks way across and scoops a full delivery from just outside off comfortably over short fine leg
misses this offcutter outside off, Wade misses both sets of stumps with the throw as they sneak in the bye
slogs hard, gets it down to long off in the air
again he walks outside the stumps trying that scoop, does not get hold of it this time, off the pad
driven to extra cover, Clarke advances in aggressively but misses the pick-up
winds up and gives it a good thump as he swivels, gets one for the effort to midwicket

inn2.comm: and beats him first up, holds its line widish outside off, back of a length, Warner hops across, prods at it
nips in short of a length into the pads, away through square leg
good length, left alone with the angle outside off
down the pads, and worked wide of fine leg
shuffles across and outside off, and bends forward to defend down the pitch
pitched up, pushed hard into the pitch, fielded by a leaping Junaid in his followthrough
spins in, good length, worked in front of square
too short, sitting up outside off, Warner clobbers it past extra cover
this one was not as short, skidded on as well, Warner tried a similar shot, and mistimed it to point
straightens on middle and leg, worked to short midwicket
goes back to a length ball, which hurries on for middle, gets the bat down just in time
jabs forward to push down to long off
short of a length forced to midwicket from the crease for a sharp single
skiddy and fullish on middle and leg, stabbed down the pitch
stays back and drives on the up, straight to extra cover
drives hard but mid off slides across to save some runs, and gets the throw in quickly too, which misses at the non-striker's, Malik it was
launched in front of square leg, not that short, did not get up much, Warner arched back and heaved it over the infield
another one, Warner lofts over point now, gets forward and lifts the pitched up delivery with an open face
goes back, opens up and punches with the spin to long on
lunges forward to push a full one to the bowler
lovely, angled in on off stump, he pushes forward, and the ball spins across the edge
hello, Warner prepares himself for the switch hit, he also turns around into a right-handed batsman, Hafeez is upto it, fires it across, and Warner has to block outside his, now off, stump
pushed back to the bowler
cut to point
flat, good length, punched to extra cover off the back foot
drives off the front foot to wide long off
flat, shortish, and fired in, pulled straight to short fine leg, lucky for the bowler
quick and spinning in, pushed to short midwicket
that is really fast, short of a length, bouncing, defended to leg
Warner ruins what had turned out to be a tight over, goes down on a knee and slog-sweeps hard and miles over deep square leg
now Hussey with the slog-sweep, aggressive approach from Australia against spin, flighted, just outside off, Hussey lunges forward, bends the knee and mows it over deep midwicket
flicked with the spin behind square leg
and again, the intent is clear from Australia, another slog-sweep, reaching out farther forward, fetching it further outside off, and depositing it over deep midwicket
worked to deep square leg
makes room to a skiddy one on middle and punches hard to extra cover
thick inside edge as he tentatively pokes across at one outside off, away to short fine leg
thick inside edge of a drive to short midwicket
another attempted extra-cover drive, again to short midwicket, who dives to stop it
pitched up, eases it straight down the ground to long off
miscues another slog-sweep this time, through with the shot too early, off the toe end of the bat, and falling short of short midwicket
fired in flat and shortish, punched back to the bowler
very fast outside off, he adjusts to push out to covers
had a thought about the slog sweep again, then saw it bowled across from round the stumps, tried to push at it, beaten
false shot, but just over mid off, reaches out to a flighted ball and pushes it in the air, Junaid tried but could not get to the ball
in the air again, this time just past Hafeez and to long on
stands several feet outside leg, the ball arrives on middle and leg, pushed to covers
fired in, rolls off the pads to square leg, some confusion as they go for the single
defended off the front foot
dropped Afridi at mid on, Hussey heaves a flighted ball, it flies in the air, Afridi leaps high and gets both hands to it, it pops out
walks across and down the pitch, defends
appeal for leg before turned down, hit on the pads as he misses a slog-sweep, was headed down leg
pushed to covers

gone, too much of the same thing, fired in just shortish, Warner winds up for another heave, but the ball bounces and gets slightly big on him, and mid on runs back to take it over his head, Rehman is pumped up
flighted full on middle and leg, whipped to midwicket
uses his feet right away, and eases it to long on with the spin
goes back to force it behind square leg
comes down the pitch again, finds midwicket from outside off
fired in down the pads, worked behind square leg, man from the deep runs across hard and keeps them to one
pulled hard over midwicket, long on cuts it off, Hussey has to hurry back for the second
length ball whipped through square leg
drives a flighted full ball past the bowler's dive to long off
down the pitch, it is fired in full, and he gets enough on it to tickle it fine down leg
delays the drive for a bit as this one is bowled slightly slower and finds extra cover
pushed to extra cover
some width outside off, punched to sweeper cover
bowled full on the stumps, whipped to midwicket
into the pads, nudged fine down leg
tossed up full, eased down to long on
straightens outside off, punched out to sweeper cover
appeal for leg before, Clarke uncertainly pushing forward, pad first and then bat as it skids on, looked to be hit clearly outside the line of off though
down the track next ball and whips in front of square leg
hurled in full, hit back hard, fielded awkwardly
pitched up and driven solidly to mid on with the angle
he's hit that really hard, pitched up full and wide outside off, slow, Clarke delays the shot and lofts it cleanly over mid off for a one-bounce four
opens the face and runs it wide of third man, they go back for the second, Hussey wold have been gone had the throw hit
pushes a full one down to long off
slams a wide and full one to the right of sweeper cover
right forward to defend down the pitch
leaves the crease to a tossed up ball and defends
skips out, drives wide of sweeper cover, makes Hussey go for the second again, the throw hits this time, but Hussey is safely in
down the track again, drives hard down the pitch, Afridi stops it
straightens outside off, chops the cut to point
drives a tossed up ball to mid off
pitched up, he gets forward and drives down to long off
steered to third man for one
down the track, and pushes a length ball to mid on
driven very hard, angled across widish, Clarke reaches out and slams it out of the reach of sweeper cover
reaches out again and pushes down to long off
tries to pull a short ball but it whizzes past
turns in from outside off, pushed with a straight bat to midwicket

ripper of a doosra, and Clarke has no answer, plays for the turn and overbalances as he comes forward, the ball just misses off, Kamran fails to gather it, Clarke's foot could have been in the air, very briefly
hares down the track, and the ball rolls to leg off pad
skiddy one worked square on the leg side
hangs in the air for a bit and goes straight, Hussey had no idea, and ended up prodding inside the line

big offspinner, appeal for leg before, seemed to have been struck outside the line of off as he came across and outside, they confer about a review, Kamran does not look convinced, and they decide against it
and Clarke takes him on right away, skips out, get to the pitch, and whips it from off high over midwicket
almost pushed straight back to the bowler, comes out, and pushes at a fullish one, the ball bounces inches before Rehman's hands
defended solidly off the front foot
starts to come out, stops as it is bowled flat, and runs it to point
fired in full, worked to deep square
straighter one bouncing around off, defended quietly

got him, that instinct for skipping out gets the captain, sharp work from Kamran, Clarke misses the work to leg as the good length offbreak spins in past his pads, and Kamran is in position to take the ball and whip the bails off, Ajmal was sure immediately that was gone, Clarke is furious as he walks back
pushes forward and eases it to a diving extra cover
pushed out to backward point
punched from the crease to mid off

has to be close, appeal for lbw turned down by umpire Bowden, Pakistan decide no to review, that looked gone on first look, and replays show Pakistan should have reviewed it, Hussey going back to one that skidded in from a length from round the stumps, and caught in front of leg and middle deep in the crease, does not seem to be an inside edge, wow, what a miss
defended off the front foot
spinning in from outside off, worked to midwicket
worked to midwicket from deep in the crease
pushed back to the bowler
flat and quick, played out to midwicket
skidding in around off, punched to the bowler off the back foot
doosra, this is really a masterclass, straightens sharply outside off, Hussey reaching forward inside the line, beaten
works an offspinner behind square leg
uncertain which way it is going, late on the offbreak, pushed back to the bowler
offspinner punched back to the bowler from the crease
good work, keeps Mike on strike, as he puts his boot out to a drive down the track
drives a full ball down to long off
and he is welcomed first ball with a huge slog-sweep, full on middle and off, and carted high over deep midwicket, onto the roof, how many balls will we lose today?
punched to long on
punched to covers from the crease
worked in front of square leg off the pad
straightens on middle, defended to leg
defended down the track
one more six, this time off Ajmal, leans forward to a full offbreak and lofts it very cleanly, superb timing, over deep midwicket
shuffles across and works to midwicket
goes across and punches an offbreak down the pitch

Ajmal has one more, and David Hussey's perky innings is over, leaned forward for the strike over deep midwicket again, but found wide long on instead, credit to Ajmal for tossing it up again after being hit for six earlier in the over
almost got the brother next ball, reaches forward tentatively to a tossed up offspinner, edged with soft hands short of slip
worked behind square leg for one
fine scrambling stop to his left from Hafeez to stop a firm push
floated up full on leg, defended
appeal for lbw from Hafeez now, two sounds as Hussey went back in the crease, looked to be an inside edge
drives a full ball to long off
punched from the crease wide of covers

not given, another leg before appeal turned down by umpire Bowden, huge offspinner turns in and strikes him on pad in the crease, could have been headed down leg with the angle, it was, as replays show, fine decision not to review
wants to paddle now from outside off, misses, and is hit on the pad
punched to midwicket
straight on now outside off, he shuffles across and is beaten as he prods inside the line

confusion, too much confusion, they have no clue what is hitting them, Australia, trying the sweep as a release stroke, doosra again, straightens on the middle stump, gloved in the air, slip has already moved to leg slip in anticipation of the sweep, the ball goes towards where he was originally, Kamran does well to react quickly, move to his right and take it
hello, another lbw appeal, and another one turned down, and again Pakistan don't review, Wade goes back in the crease and is caught on the pad, was that sliding down? yes, it was
quick and full on the stumps, blocked
spins in a tad from outside off, defended
quick and worked out to square leg
a slower legbreak now, spins in and bounces from the rough outside off, beats him on the cut
pushed hard down to long on
left alone outside off
punched  back to the bowler
another one forced down, this time to long on
worked to midwicket
goes deep to work it in front of square leg
length ball punched down the track from the crease
Afridi dives to his left trying to stop the push, he goes at it right-handed, the left one is injured, midwicket backs up
pulled to deep midwicket
bowled quick and flat outside off, punched through point
bends his knee, swivels and swings it around the corner to fine leg
driven hard down to sweeper cover
that was fast, that was hurled in at some pace, pushed to the off side
leans forward to defend to extra cover
didn't carry to slip, lovely delivery, drifts in, turns across the forward push, takes the edge, but falls short of Misbah, who smiles calmly
top-edged sweep off one fired in, fine leg is deep
punched off the back foot to extra cover
punched from the crease to long off
hangs in the air for a bit more, defended down the pitch off a thick inside edge
that is a fast bowler's delivery, 125 kph, fullish length, pushed back to the bowler
flat, swept to short fine leg
slightly slower, just under 100 kph by Boom Boom standards, defended off the front foot
lot slower, tossed up too, eased down to long on
down to long on for one more
opens the face and runs it to backward point
down the track and pushes to long on
full, pushed to the bowler
full again, driven to long off
lunges forward to defend
looks to sweep a full toss, inside edge past the stumps down leg
floated across, and that has been crashed through extra cover, past the dive of the fielder in the ring
full ball slapped away to extra cover
squeezed out, again to extra cover
swept hard, through the square leg umpire's legs for four
turning in a bit from outside off, patted back to the bowler
phew, he is just hurling them in, stabbed towards short third man
nudged softly in front of square leg
works a tossed up full ball to midwicket
seemed like a wrong 'un, played out softly
straightens on off, patted back off the front foot,
and Kamran misses a stumping, Wade walks out to one going down leg quickly, but Kamran fails to gather, Azhar has his hand on his face in anguish
smashes the sweep off a full ball on leg behind square
swept again, through square leg
works a tossed up ball from outside off through midwicket
slapped off the back foot, Misbah gets down to his right to field
drives a full ball to long on
rocks back and pulls hard to deep square
cuts a flat delivery well to backward point, fine stop by Hafeez
full on leg, worked through square
knocked down to long on for a single
hit hard down the ground, good stop by the bowler to his right
eases a flighted ball angled across past point
he tries a forcing reverse sweep now, from around leg stump, and gets it past short third man who pulls it back late with a slide near the rope
played out softly towards point
full, driven down to long off
another easy single to long on
spins in sharply, worked to square leg
full toss now and it is clipped forcingly through midwicket
wide one floated across, carved to sweeper cover
low full toss pushed to long off
that was very fast, angled across on a length, widish outside off, and steered past short third man, not been a happy day for Afridi
goes across and pushes a length ball sliding in, down the track
appeal for lbw as he misses the sweep, going down leg as it was angled in from over the stumps
there is the breakthrough, Rehman has done it for Pakistan, big gap between bat and pad as Wade pushes forward eagerly to a flighted length ball, it spins in through the gate and strikes off
defended off the front foot around middle
fired in flat and worked behind square leg, who dives to stop the ball with one hand, Imran Farhat
worked straight to midwicket
pushed off the front foot towwards covers

appeal from the keeper for leg before, not from the bowler, that looked very close, hit in front of middle as this one straightened sharply from middle and leg, was it too high? ball tracker says it was
down the track and lofted on the bounce to long off
pulled hard behind square leg
worked to short fine leg off the pad
misses the sweep as this one is floated full on the pads, and off them fine down leg
worked down to long on from the crease
full one worked through midwicket
low full toss hit down to long on
worked from outside off to square leg, Farhat charges in but misses the pick-up
hit on the pad first ball as he fails to work an offspinner to leg, bounces onto his chin
pushed to extra cover, direct hit at the striker's, but Maxweel has made his ground long back
straightens on middle, and worked through midwicket
punches an offspinner in front of square on off, Rehman's dive cannot stop the ball
plays the tossed up doosra well, drives to sweeper cover with an open face
offspinner around off, eases it with an open face to point
well done, sweeping powerfully from outside off, in the air and in the gap between deep square and deep midwicket
pushed back to the bowler
now he reverse sweeps, set himself up early, and dispatched it past short third man, that is fifty for Hussey
played out to midwicket
another one, reverse paddle from outside off, Afridi after it from short third man, slides and pulls it back in, but he seems to have touched the rope

worked in front of square leg
slapped away to sweeper cover

throws his bat at a full one outside off, thick edge flies past short third man, Afridi on his haunches
straightens on middle, opens the face and runs it to point, direct hit would have been close for Hussey
offspinner rolls off the pad square to leg
offbreak turns in, carefully dabbed to short third man
fired in wide down the leg side
delays the forward movement to a tossed up offspinner and pushes it towards covers for a sharp run, throw misses again

there is the tossed up doosra, and this time Kamran is sharp in taking the bails off, Maxwell lured out in a forward prod, the ball sneaks past the outside edge, the back foot, to me, seems to be slightly in the air as Kamran takes the bails off, it is the replay from the stumps that seems to be suggesting that, although the side angle is inconclusive, batsman gets the benefit of doubt
charges out a to a flighted, full and wide one and drills it through extra cover, it slows up near the rope
swings a sweep flat and on the bounce to deep square leg
that is big, he has got down on a knee and swung a full delivery powerfully behind square leg, and it has gone all the way
Afridi has had a forgettable game, a late dab this time to send the ball racing past short third man
pushed towards point, Malik slips as he runs in, they complete the single safely
slower through the air, played out to midwicket
full outside off and Afridi goes for four more, reverse sweep again from Hussey, what a gem he's played, always in control of the stroke, past short third man
full one patted down the track
spins in sharply and hits him on the pad in the crease, going down leg
opens the face slightly, he has looked alright against the doosra, runs it towards third man
appeal for caught-and-bowled, Ajmal runs forward to take the ball as it pops up off pad as Maxwell pushes out
defends the flighted doosra softly and late off the front foot
gets it very full and drills it down to long on
dropped, Pakistan falling apart now, short ball pulled off the front foot straight to Azhar at deep midwicket, he scrambles awkwardly and puts it down
drives a full ball to short extra cover
that is an ugly swipe from Hussey to give it away, charges out to a length ball, makes some room and has a big heave, misses and is bowled

Maxwell impresses again, gets front foot out to a flighted one outside off and lofts it cleanly all the way over extra cover with a straight followthrough

and again, through extra cover, Clarke claps in the pavilion as Maxwell gets inside the line of a tossed up doosra on middle, exposes all the stumps, and drills it past extra cover, boy, he is playing Ajmal like he has dealt with him for years
defended solidly off the front foot
Christian holes out needlessly, tries to loft a length ball over mid off, gets a lot of height, and that is all he gets, Farhat settles under it at mid off
Maxwell keeps clobbering them, on the front foot, swings a length ball hard behind square leg
he has a heave at this pitched up ball, thick inside edge to deep midwicket, the Australia dressing room claps whole-heartedly, for Maxwell's maiden ODI 50
full into the pads, worked to fine leg
opens the face and drills a full delivery hard to point
there it is, Maxwell launches a full slower one high over wide long on as Australia takes the series 2-1, sees it disappear, pumps his fist and roars
